com.kauailabs.sf2.pose

Class Pose

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kauailabs.sf2.pose.Pose
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IInterpolate<Pose>, ICopy<Pose>, IQuantity

    public class Pose
extends java.lang.Object
implements IInterpolate<Pose>, ICopy<Pose>, IQuantity
    The Pose class represents a 2-dimensional position, and a 3-dimensional orientation at a given instant in time. Note that the Pose class also provides a timestamp, representing the sensor timestamp for the "master timestamp clock source". In addition to representing a pose, the Pose class can also represent an amount of change in pose, in which case the timestamp represents the duration of time comprising that position and orientation motion.
